Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's start from the top."
Authority: The final word on this matter has been spoken.
You: "We're not any closer to knowing *how* they heard it, though, are we?"
You: "Spooky shit. But what does it... mean?" (Squint in thought.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't know what to say to that, or what you want me to say. I'm sorry."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Did we ask where the kids were when they heard the voice?" The wind picks up, blowing a stray strand of the lieutenant's hair out of place. He smooths it back.
"When you first spoke to the twins, did you ask them where they were when they heard the voice?" The wind picks up, blowing a stray strand of the lieutenant's hair out of place. He smooths it back.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We could ask where the kids were when it happened."
Kim Kitsuragi: "And, detective..." He turns to you. He smiles. "Thanks for this. It's been interesting."
He nods curtly toward the coast. "Whenever you're ready," he says coldly.
You: "I mean, a weird voice in *my* head said to talk to the kids. Maybe it's related?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I don't think the voices in your head are related to this, no."
You: "I didn't. Sorry."
Kim Kitsuragi: "No need to apologize. I was just going to say it'd be a good idea to ask them."

You: "Nope."

You: "Hold up, Kim. Aren't you going to say anything about meeting your radio heroes?"

Kim Kitsuragi: "No... We're not." The lieutenant's gaze travels toward the coast, toward the fishing village so far away.
